question: Aditya Lpu: A Comprehensive Summary of Quantum Machine Learning
answer: Umyal Dixit: In this video, they dive deep into quantum machine learning, an entirely new field of study that merges quantum computing with machine learning into one powerful new future. Quantum computing is the result of the rules of quantum mechanics and deals with qubits instead of regular bits, which at all times can be in every state simultaneously. Now referred to as superposition, this phenomenon allows quantum computers to process information at unbelievable speeds-way faster than traditional computers for certain kinds of tasks. Meanwhile, machine learning is a subfield of AI in which computers learn from data, recognize patterns, and improve over time-all without explicit programming.
